trans-unit.id: Client authentication failed (e.g., unknown client, no client authentication included, or unsupported authentication method). The authorization server MAY return an HTTP 401 (Unauthorized) status code to indicate which HTTP authentication schemes are supported. If the client attempted to authenticate via the "Authorization" request header field, the authorization server MUST respond with an HTTP 401 (Unauthorized) status code and include the "WWW-Authenticate" response header field matching the authentication scheme used by the client.
trans-unit.source: Client authentication failed (e.g., unknown client, no client authentication included, or unsupported authentication method). The authorization server MAY return an HTTP 401 (Unauthorized) status code to indicate which HTTP authentication schemes are supported. If the client attempted to authenticate via the "Authorization" request header field, the authorization server MUST respond with an HTTP 401 (Unauthorized) status code and include the "WWW-Authenticate" response header field matching the authentication scheme used by the client.
trans-unit.target: L'authentification du client a échoué (par exemple, client inconnu, aucune identification de client incluse ou méthode d’identification non prise en charge). Le serveur d'autorisation PEUT renvoyer un code d'état HTTP 401 (non autorisé) pour indiquer quels schémas d'authentification HTTP sont pris en charge. Si le client tente de s'authentifier via le champ d'en-tête de demande "Authorization", le serveur d'autorisation DOIT répondre avec un code d'état HTTP 401 (non autorisé) et inclure le champ d'en-tête de réponse "WWW-Authenticate" correspondant au schéma d'authentification utilisé par le client.
